The paper deals with deep neural networks and their convergence speed and robustness, which are topics typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on activation functions, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Additionally, the paper introduces a new normalization technique, which falls under the category of optimization and regularization methods, studied in the statistical learning (cs.SI) sub-category.
